For further reading, here are some amazing references
1. Yann LeCun et al., 1998, Gradient-Based Learning Applied to Document Recognition
2. Jianxin Wu, 2017, Introduction to Convolutional Neural Networks
3. C.-C. Jay Kuo, 2016, Understanding Convolutional Neural Networks with A Mathematical Model
4. Kaiming He et al., 2015, Delving Deep into Rectifiers: Surpassing Human-Level Performance on ImageNet Classification
5. Dominik Scherer et al., 2010, Evaluation of Pooling Operations in Convolutional Architectures for Object Recognition
6. Adit Deshpande, 2016, The 9 Deep Learning Papers You Need To Know About (Understanding CNNs Part 3)
7. Rob DiPietro, 2016, A Friendly Introduction to Cross-Entropy Loss
8. Peter Roelants, 2016, How to implement a neural network Intermezzo 2

Source: Superdatascience.com
